OL,3,CCan public inquiries lead to real
OL,4,Cchange?
OL,6,FWhile public inquiries can be tools
OL,7,Ffor accountability, they are not
OL,8,Fwithout challenges. Critics often
OL,9,Fpoint to the lengthy durations and
OL,10,Fsubstantial costs associated with
OL,11,Fthese investigations and even more
OL,12,Fcrucially the fact they often do not
OL,13,Flead to change.
OL,15,FA recent report by the House of Lords
OL,16,FStatutory Inquiries Committee warned
OL,17,Finquiries were perceived as
OL,18,F"frequently too long and expensive,
OL,19,Fleading to a loss of public confidence
OL,20,Fand protracted trauma".
