OL,3,CCan public inquiries lead to real
OL,4,Cchange?
OL,6,FFigen Murray said: They're crucially
OL,7,Fimportant because they make people
OL,8,Faccountable and they actually make
OL,9,Fsure all the facts are on the table
OL,10,Fand people can examine them and
OL,11,Factually make sense of what happened
OL,12,Fand it puts all the pieces together
OL,13,Fthat are missing.
OL,15,F"I think inquiries are absolutely
OL,16,Fcrucial to learning from bad
OL,17,Fcatastrophic events and finding out
OL,18,Fwhat can be done to avoid that from
OL,19,Fhappening again."
