OL,3,CCan public inquiries lead to real
OL,4,Cchange?
OL,6,F"There are two big reasons why I think
OL,7,Fthey are ineffective," he said.
OL,9,F"The first-is the lack of a duty of
OL,10,Fcandour so it is easy to mislead a
OL,11,Fpublic inquiry - certainly in the
OL,12,Fearly stages before an inquiry kicks
OL,13,Foff and the second is a lack of any
OL,14,Foversight mechanism to see that any
OL,15,Frecommendations are, if not fully
OL,16,Fimplemented, then at least properly
OL,17,Fconsidered.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/10
